<br>
60 Water pet always has been very close to epic pets melee ability. I remember parses posted months ago of epic and water against shrooms in FG and in those I think a maxed water actually outmeleed the epic (in any case the results where nearly the same melee dps so statistical errors could account for the small difference).<br>
<br>
The highest level mob I've routinely seen Epic land procs on is 60. My epic was landing procs on even cons in ToV yesterday and he routinely lands procs on the Lvl 60 nameds in Umbral (assuming they are susceptable to cold). I cannot recall him landing procs on Lvl 61+ ToV mobs with any regularity, if at all.<br>
<br>
I think pet levels need to be upped (especially epic now that all pets are summoned at Lvl 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  so that at least the spells and procs at least stand a chance of landing on the 65+ mobs.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucydmab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 542<br> <font color=#333333>(7/29/02 10:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=610.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: epic pet.. </span><hr size=1> I also ran these tests prior to and after the patches (I got the logs somewhere arounds here, I never bothered posting them since the end result in my mind wasn't too exciting (epic pet still better than water pet)). Basic result was the same: (max) water pet dps and epic pet dps were essentially the same. In one sense the epic pet gained some ground because it's damage got raised to 79 while water pet's max is still 68 (70 focused). So first off: water pet meele dps from the rear has ALWAYS been in parity with epic pet (although one had to do some work to get a max or near max hitting pet before)<br>
<br>
For those that don't know, pets do not proc on level 61+ mobs. They'll land procs like crazy on level 60 mobs, but do absolutely nothing on a level 61. <br>
<br>
I have never seen any evidence anywhere that water pet and epic pet's underlying attack characteristics were different. Same % hit rates, same percentage of max damage average hits. Essentially the water pet does just over 10% less damage per hit (70 max versus 79 max), but gains backstabs which roughly cancel out the lost damage.<br>
<br>
Let's not forget for soloing and grouping, epic pet BLOWS AWAY water pet (and most of the other pets 95% of the time) because of procs, damage shield, stuns, and extra hit points. Furthermore, on raids in guilds with pre- SoDs or luclin-weapons, the epic pet is likely to be one of the highest taunt entities fighting the mob. This means nukers and healers can manage aggro relative to the pet, as opposed to a warrior wielding epics or something.<br>
<br>
So, let's see, in a guild with uber equipped level 60 warriors, on raids against level 61+ mobs, on the fraction of mobs where it is easy to get the pet behind the monster, and when the mage is level 60, THEN the mage can summon a pet (GV focused water) with simular effectiveness to a mage with an epic pet.  I see *no* problem with this state of affairs. Hell, how many level 60 non-epiced mages are there in guilds with the warriors wielding SoDs or better? If there are any, they are probally feeling gimp enough as it is; do you really want to nerf GV water further relative to the epic pet?<br>
<br>
About the only buff to the epic pet I'd like to see is allow his procs to land on any level mob; I personally find the level 60 mob cut off to be arbitrary, and possibly even a bug/oversight ala the haste cap. This would also have no effect on soloing and almost no effect on exp groups. <p>Sage Cydmab Promethean <BR>
Arch Mage of Morell Thule <BR>
