<br>
So imho the real discussion to have here is : How should lvl 60 water pet compare to epic melee-wise.<br>
<br>
My quick answer is i'd expect greater voc. water to be very close to epic pet melee wise. Wich he is. <br>
<br>
My longer answer is while I can live easily with equal MELEE dmg output, imho a mage with epic should have a little edge over a non epic mage in the high end raiding game. This is not really happening since at that level the damage output will come primarily from melee. <br>
<br>
Since raising melee output of epic would also affect a lot of other situation where he's already dominant, we need to look elsewhere imho. The simplest way I could see is to make pet be able to land procs on raid level mobs, eighter by &quot;fakin&quot; they are higher level when they cast/proc, or by making proc lure type, or by removing whatever is preventing pet spell output to land.<br>
<br>
And also eighter fix air pet damage a bit or make him a KICK ASS tanking pet.<br>
